Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay fine, micaceous, red-brown. Rectangular stamp with Greek inscription.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary 1884-5 (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 51,15, 59 21 or 91, 6 (one of which is probably Ashmolean Museum, 1888.199d).
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.1602)
